@*
    Unit-aware read-only display for forms. Sits next to a label the
    way <UnitInput> does on editable rows, but renders the value as a
    semantic <output> element rather than a disabled <input> or a div
    pretending to be one. Screen readers identify <output> as a live
    result region; sighted users see the same dimmed background as a
    disabled input.

    Used on every "computed (read-only)" field on edit pages where
    the value is owned by Calculate / the auto-calc and shouldn't be
    typed into. Replaces the prior pattern:

        <div class="enki-form-input" style="background: ...">
            <UnitFormatted Value="@x" Quantity="..." />
        </div>

    …which was a div masquerading as an input — visually fine but
    semantically wrong.

    All parameters except Value + Quantity are passed through to the
    inner <UnitFormatted>; the wrapper just adds the readout styling.
*@

<output class="@CssClass enki-mono enki-form-readout"
        aria-label="@AriaLabel">
    <UnitFormatted Value="@Value"
                   Quantity="@Quantity"
                   Format="@Format"
                   ShowUnit="@ShowUnit"
                   OverrideUnit="@OverrideUnit"
                   OverrideAbbreviation="@OverrideAbbreviation" />
</output>

